The '''United States Senate election of 1872''' was an election which had the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]], while still retaining a commanding majority, lose nine seats in the [[United States Senate]], mostly as defections to the [[Liberal Republican Party (United States)|Liberal Republican Party]].  It also coincided with President [[Ulysses S. Grant|Ulysses S. Grant's]] easy [[United States presidential election, 1872|re-election]].

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

==Results==
Senate Party Division, [[43rd United States Congress|43rd Congress]] (1873â1875)

* Majority Party: Republican (47)
* Minority Party: Democratic (19)
* Other Parties: Liberal Republican (7)
* '''Total Seats: 74'''

